    "EMC (Expected Model Change): EMC selects samples based on the expected change in the model's output.",
    "It is a forward-looking approach that prioritizes samples anticipated to have the greatest impact on the model's future learning trajectory.",
    "Bayesian Generative AL: This method employs Bayesian generative models for sample selection, focusing on the probabilistic modeling of data.",
    "It is particularly effective in scenarios where understanding the underlying data generation process is crucial for sample selection.",
